# BizCode DevOps Standards
# Senior DevOps Engineer Rules & Best Practices
# Date: 2026-04-17

## 1. CONTAINERIZATION (Issue #201, #202)

### Docker for Express API

```dockerfile
FROM node:22-alpine AS builder
WORKDIR /app
COPY package*.json ./
RUN npm ci
COPY . .
RUN npm run type-check && npm run lint && npm run test

FROM node:22-alpine AS runtime
WORKDIR /app
COPY package*.json ./
RUN npm ci --omit=dev
COPY server ./server
COPY prisma ./prisma
EXPOSE 3001
HEALTHCHECK --interval=10s CMD node -e "require('http').get('http://localhost:3001/health', (r) => { if (r.statusCode!==200) throw new Error(r.statusCode); })"
CMD ["npm", "run", "server"]
```

### Docker Compose for Local Dev

```yaml
version: '3.8'
services:
  postgres:
    image: postgres:16-alpine
    environment:
      POSTGRES_USER: bizcode
      POSTGRES_PASSWORD: bizcode
      POSTGRES_DB: bizcode_dev
    volumes:
      - postgres_data:/var/lib/postgresql/data
    ports:
      - "5432:5432"
    healthcheck:
      test: ["CMD-SHELL", "pg_isready -U bizcode"]
      interval: 10s

  api:
    build: .
    environment:
      DATABASE_URL: postgresql://bizcode:bizcode@postgres:5432/bizcode_dev
    ports:
      - "3001:3001"
    depends_on:
      postgres:
        condition: service_healthy
    volumes:
      - .:/app
```

**Never hardcode secrets in Dockerfile or compose file.**

