## 4. LOGGING (Issue #209)

### Structured Logging Format

**Rule:** Every log entry has: timestamp, level, service, requestId, message.

```json
{
  "timestamp": "2026-04-17T10:30:00Z",
  "level": "info",
  "service": "bizcode-api",
  "requestId": "req_123abc",
  "userId": "user_456",
  "tenantId": "tenant_789",
  "message": "Invoice created",
  "duration_ms": 245,
  "data": { "invoiceId": "inv_123", "total": 5000 }
}
```

**When to log:**
- Request arrival (INFO)
- Request completion (INFO with duration)
- Database errors (ERROR with query)
- Business events (INFO: "cliente created", "invoice paid")
- Validation failures (WARN)
- Unexpected errors (ERROR with stack trace)

**Never log:**
- Passwords
- API keys / tokens
- Full credit cards (log last 4 digits only)
- SSN / CUIT / PII
- Full email addresses (log hash)

