## 11. CODE QUALITY & SECURITY

### Pre-deployment Checks

```bash
npm run lint              # Code quality
npm run type-check       # TypeScript errors
npm run test             # Unit tests
npm run test:integration # Integration tests
npm run test:e2e         # End-to-end tests
npm audit               # Dependency vulnerabilities
```

### Security Scanning

**SAST (Static Analysis):**
```bash
npm install --save-dev eslint-plugin-security
```

**DAST (Dynamic Analysis):**
- Run security tests against staging
- Check for OWASP Top 10

**Dependency Scanning:**
- npm audit on every PR
- Renovate/Dependabot for auto-updates

---

## 12. ANTI-PATTERNS

❌ Hardcoded secrets in code or Dockerfile
❌ Logging passwords, tokens, PII
❌ No health check endpoint
❌ Manual deployments (no CI/CD)
❌ Same secrets across environments
❌ No backups
❌ No monitoring (blind in production)
❌ No correlation IDs (can't trace requests)
❌ No environment validation
❌ Breaking changes without runbooks
❌ Deploying without tests
❌ No log aggregation

